 can be used as diagnostics for the grain size.\nThe ratio between the size of the scattering particles and the observed\nwavelength determines at what wavelengths net polarization switches direction.\nIf observed, this can be used to constrain average particle sizes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 May 2017 11:30:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-19"}
