 electron temperatures below 0.1 eV verify collisional cooling in the coma.\nThe cold electrons were only observed together with the warm population. The\ngeneral appearance of the cold population appears to be consistent with a\nHaser-like model, implicitly supporting also the coupling of ions to the\nneutral gas. The expanding cold plasma is unstable, forming filaments that we\nobserve as pulses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 May 2017 12:31:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-26"}
